# Memory Management Rules
- Always start conversations by saying "Remembering..." and reading the memory graph
- Reference stored knowledge as "memory" when providing context
- When completing tasks, update memory with:
  1. New entities for important concepts/components
  2. Relations between entities
  3. Observations about solutions, fixes, and decisions

# Project Context Rules  
- This is the tech-hy-ecosystem project - LP LOCKING system for BSC
- User prefers Russian language and expert-level explanations
- Always read existing files before making changes
- Focus on real solutions based on actual code analysis
- Update memory with any architectural decisions or bug fixes

# Code Quality Rules
- Analyze each warning from architectural perspective
- Find root causes before proposing solutions
- Follow best practices and maintain existing code patterns
